
@startuml
' Class Diagram for Tourist Attractions System

class City {
  -name: String
  -inhabitants: Integer
}

class Attraction {
  -name: String
  -address: String
}

class GuidedTour {
  -duration: Integer
  -maxVisitors: Integer = 20
  -discountAmount: Double
}

class Visitor {
  -name: String
}

class Guide {
  -name: String
}

' Associations

City "1" -- "0..*" Attraction : has

Attraction "1" -- "0..*" GuidedTour : offers

GuidedTour "1" -- "0..20" Visitor : includes
GuidedTour "1" -- "1" Guide : requires

@enduml

### Explanation of the Diagram:
- **`City`** contains multiple **`Attraction`** instances.
- Each **`Attraction`** can offer multiple **`GuidedTour`** instances.
- Each **`GuidedTour`** has a fixed maximum of 20 **`Visitor`**s and is led by one **`Guide`**.
- A **`GuidedTour`** may have a discount amount, which applies to certain visitors.
- Both **`Visitor`** and **`Guide`** are people with names.

